goals do
  goal "熟悉瀏覽器的開發人員工具。它們是你繼續建構 HTML、CSS 及 Javascript 知識很好的起點。"
  tip "底下的截圖都是以 Chrome 瀏覽為例，該瀏覽器在 Mac、Windows 及 Linux 環境都能用，且有非常棒的開發人員工具。若你偏好其它瀏覽器，通常你也可以找到類似的一組工具來用。"
end

steps do

  step do
    message <<-MARKDOWN
      首先，你得打開你的開發人員工具。它們預設是隱藏起來的。

      <img src='/frontend/img/devtools.png'>

      在 Chrome 裡面，你可以透過點擊 _檢視 > 開發人員選項 > 開發人員工具_來開啟。
    MARKDOWN
  end

  step do
    message <<-MARKDOWN
      點擊 「Elements」來檢視你的 HTML。

      <img src='/frontend/img/devtools_elements.png'>

      點選元件裡的 HTML 標籤會使該元件在瀏覽器視窗裡變得顯眼。這是樣式方面問題除錯的利器。在面板的右邊，你甚至可以看到一串該元件使用的樣式。
    MARKDOWN
    tip "Chrome 的 Element 面板會在你用 Javascript 改變 DOM 時更新並顯示 DOM 最新的狀態。有些 Elements 面板做不到這點 &mdash; 它們只單純顯示頁面剛讀進來時 HTML 的樣子。"
  end

  step do
    message <<-MARKDOWN
      在 「Network」面板裡，你可以看到你的 HTML 面頁正在讀哪些其它檔案與資源。

      <img src='/frontend/img/devtools_network.png'>

      如果你點選一個檔案名稱，你可以看到該檔案的內容。This panel is a great place for debugging script linking or loading issues. (You can see HTTP headers and request params here too, with a little digging.)
    MARKDOWN
  end

  step do
    message <<-MARKDOWN
      The 'Console' is the JavaScript developer's secret weapon. It lets you run JavaScript by typing it in directly &mdash; and it runs your scripts _in the context of your page_, so you can interact directly with objects and functions you've defined. It's helpful for debugging and experimenting.

      <img src='/frontend/img/devtools_console.png'>
    MARKDOWN
  end

  step do
    message <<-MARKDOWN
      The 'Sources' panel is another JavaScript pro tool. If you're used to working with an IDE (Integrated Development Environment) that has a debugger, you'll be able to use many of the same techniques (like breakpoints, stack traces, and watch expressions) right here in the browser.

      <img src='/frontend/img/devtools_script.png'>
    MARKDOWN
  end
end

explanation do

  message <<-MARKDOWN

## Keep Learning with Developer Tools

With good browser developer tools, you can pick apart every website you visit. If you see cool
CSS styles or JavaScript animations, you can always look under the hood and figure out how
they're done. It's a great way to keep learning as a front-end developer.

  MARKDOWN
end
